ed and the subject suffers      or doesn't like it.</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="33%" height="17"><div align="right">        <p align="right"><span class="style1">N1</span> は／が <span class="style3">N2</span> <br>        </p>    </div></td>    <td colspan="2"><p>に (by)<br>        から (from) </p></td>    <td width="38%"> + <span class="style2">passive form of verb </span></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="17" colspan="4"><p>兄はケーキを食べた。[ transitve verb]        --&gt; <span class="style1"><br>      私</span>は<span class="style3">兄</span>に        ケーキを<span class="style2">食べられた</span>。[indirect            passive] My brother ate (my) cake, and I am upset. <br>            雨がふっています。[intransitive verb]--&gt;<br>            <span class="style1">私</span>は<span class="style3">雨に</span><span class="style2">ふられました</span>。[indirect            passive] It rained, and I didn't like it.<br>            私のいぬが死んだ。--&gt;<span class="style3">私のいぬに</span>死なれた。[indirect passive]            My dog died, and I am suffering from it. <br>    </p>      </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="17" colspan="4"><ul>      <li>Indirect passive sentences can have  D.O. </li>    <li>Indirect passive sentences can be formed with transitive verb and intransitive      verb. </li>    </ul></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="17" colspan="4"><img src="../../../../images/ｇvideo.jpg" alt="video icon" width="22" height="16">　Example:      <a href="../../../gvideo/suffierpassive.mov" target="_blank">movie &quot; Ruble's Horrible, Terrible, No Good, Very Bad Day&quot;</a> </td>  </tr></table><br><table width="90%" border="1" align="center">  <tr>    <td height="19" colspan="2" bgcolor="#CCCCCC">Active sentence, direct passive      sentence, and indirect passive sentence </td>    </tr>  <tr>    <td width="27%" height="17"><div align="right">        <p align="left"><img src="../../../gimages/gi_passive_tomnezumi.jpg" width="143" height="101"></p>    </div>      </td>    <td width="73%" height="17"><p>トムはねずみをとった。</p>      <p>&nbsp;</p></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td height="61"><p><img src="../../../gimages/gi_passive_tompitchnezumi.jpg" width="222" height="171"></p></td>  <td>ピッチがねずみを食べた。Pitch ate a mouse. <br>    [active sentence]      <p> <br>        ねずみはピッチに食べられた。The mouse was eaten by Pitch. <br>  [direct passive]</p>      <p>トムはピッチにねずみを食べられた。Pitch ate a mouse, and Tom is upset.<br>        [indirect/suffering passive]<br>        </p></td>  </tr></table><p>&nbsp;</p><ul>	<LI>			<B>練習 (Practice Quizzes)</B>			<ul>			  <li><a href="../../../gquiz/y2/412l/gq_y2_412l_passivemulti.php">Passive -- multiple choices</a></li>		  <li><a href="../../../gquiz/y2/412l/gq_y2_412l_passivepart.php">Passive -- particles</a> </li>		  </ul>	</LI></LI> 			<p align="center"><a href="#top">Return to Top</a> </p> 			<p align="center"><a href="../../../../glist.php">Ｒeturn to Grammar Lists</a></p></UL>          </tr></table></BODY></HTML>